The chairman of the Arab-Islamic Rally party has  been murdered after being abducted, press reports said here Sunday.
Laid Grine, 49, who was also an Algiers lawyer, was found Saturday morning  near Algiers with his throat cut, the reports said.
The lawyer had been captured the previous day by unidentified abductors  from his house at Bordj El Mokhfi east of Algiers.
There has been no official reponse to his kidnapping and murder, but press  reports said he had succeeded Wednesday in gaining the acquittal of an Islamic  fundamentalist being tried by one of the country's special "anti-terrorism"   courts.
